<sect1 id="dir_04e46b302a6aadc7f23a11997ed7852b_1autotoc_md395">
<title>Architecture</title><para>1. <bold>GameTimer</bold> accumulates elapsed time and increments a revision counter on each update 2. <bold>TimerControlCommand</bold> is written into the command buffer to request state transitions (start, pause, stop) 3. <bold>TimerCommandDispatcher</bold> routes the command to the <bold>TimerManager</bold> via the Visitor pattern 4. <bold>TimerManager</bold> collects pending commands and applies them during <computeroutput>flush()</computeroutput> 5. <bold>GameTimerUpdateSystem</bold> advances all timers by the current delta time each frame 6. <bold>GameTimerBindingComponent</bold> allows entities to track a specific timer&apos;s revision</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="dir_04e46b302a6aadc7f23a11997ed7852b_1autotoc_md396">
<title>Integration</title><para>The timing system integrates with:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><bold>Command system</bold> - timer state transitions are requested via <computeroutput>TimerControlCommand</computeroutput></para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Manager system</bold> - <computeroutput>TimerManager</computeroutput> participates in the game loop flush cycle</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Game state listeners</bold> - can issue timer commands in response to state changes</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
